The s ame words can be used  to describe different types of concepts in free  text; for example, AP2 can be the name of a gene   (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/?term=2167 ), a chemical   (https://meshb.nlm.nih.gov/record/ui?ui=C417523 ), or a cell -line  (https://web.expasy.org/cellosaurus/CVCL_1147 ).
Conversely, the same  concepts can have different  names; for example,  the HER2 gene has at least  10 different synonyms mentioned in  text  (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/2064 ).
In addition , a bio-concept can span multip le words; for  example, serum and glucocorticoid -induced protein kinase  is the name of a gene (SGK1 ,  https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/6446 ).
We followed the  preprocessing pipeline  from [34] (the code is publicly available via https://github.com/ncbi - nlp/BioSentVec ).
